16/11/2003
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- Prime Minister Simeon Saxe-Coburg said Friday (14 November) the government plans to step up measures against organised crime. He made the pledge while answering parliamentary deputies' questions about the recent rise in the number of violent incidents. While admitting the situation was serious, he refused to bow to opposition demands for the dismissal of Interior Minister Georgi Petkanov.
In other news Friday, Bulgarian President Georgi Parvanov made a one-day visit to Slovakia. He met with his counterpart, Rudolf Schuster, who told him it was time for Slovakia to live up to its promises to support Bulgaria's EU aspirations. (Trud, 24 Chassa - 15/11/03; BTA, BNT, BNR, bTV, Nova TV- 14/11/03)
